# Right-click on a bufferline tab whose buffer is dirty now offers
# "Save" at the top of the menu. SEV-2 VS-Code-mouse hunt finding
# (2026-06-07): "No Save button anywhere — the right-click menu had
# Close/Close-others/Close-all/Copy-path but no Save."
write a.txt "alpha"
open a.txt
command view.toggle_tree

# Type into the buffer so it's dirty.
type "X"
expect dirty true

# Right-click the tab at row 1 (bufferline row), col 4 (inside tab).
rightclick 4 1
expect screen contains "Save"
expect screen contains "Close"
